HEADWORD: machine language
<hw>machine language</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>a
set of instructions{3} in a binary form that can be executed directly by
the CPU of a computer without translation by a computer
program.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> machine code, binary code.</syn>⟦br⟧
